<subSubSection id="C347EFD5FFF91568E7F21A1DFA3A3E1A" pageId="2" pageNumber="323" type="key">
<keyStep id="30A9A4FBFFF91568E7F21A1DFA3A39D0" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21A1DFA3A399F" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21A1DFA3A399F" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
1. Posterior hypopygeal margin strongly excavated, so that median area of hypopygium occupies less than half of its length (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E2171A1DFEEA399F" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Figs 4A, 4D, 4J</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E6331AF0FED2399E" box="[342,372,645,667]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,359,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-102@14.[152,1436,345,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. A–C. Pristonesia sicril sp. nov.; D–F. Pristonesia tainatril sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia uvenil sp. nov.. A, D, G. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410670/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">5D</figureCitation>
)....................................................................................... 2
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21AD6FA3A39D0" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21AD6FA3A39D0" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
- Posterior hypopygeal margin weakly emarginated, so that median area of hypopygium occupies more than half of its length (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E78C1AB5FE9F39D0" box="[233,313,704,726]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Figs 4G</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E6261ACAFE2C39D0" box="[323,394,703,725]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,359,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-102@14.[152,1436,345,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. A–C. Pristonesia sicril sp. nov.; D–F. Pristonesia tainatril sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia uvenil sp. nov.. A, D, G. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410670/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">5A, 5G</figureCitation>
)..................................................................................... 5
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30A9A4FBFFF91568E7F21AA8FA3A384F" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21AA8FA3A380A" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21AA8FA3A380A" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
2. Anterior hypopygeal margin with anteromedial apodeme (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E46E1AA8FCDE39F6" box="[779,888,733,755]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Fig. 4D, 4J</figureCitation>
); median area of hypopygium at most quarter of its length (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E78C1A8FFEFF3815" box="[233,345,762,784]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Figs 4D, 4J</figureCitation>
)......................................................................................... 3
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21B6DFA3A384F" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21B6DFA3A384F" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
- Anterior hypopygeal margin without anteromedial apodeme (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E44D1B6DFCD13828" box="[808,887,792,814]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Figs 4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E41A1B62FC063828" box="[895,928,791,813]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,359,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-102@14.[152,1436,345,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. A–C. Pristonesia sicril sp. nov.; D–F. Pristonesia tainatril sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia uvenil sp. nov.. A, D, G. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410670/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">5D</figureCitation>
); median area of hypopygium about third of its length (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E78C1B40FE9F384F" box="[233,313,821,843]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Figs 4A</figureCitation>
, 
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E6261B40FEC7384E" box="[323,353,821,843]" captionStart="FIGURE 5" captionStartId="14.[151,250,1930,1954]" captionTargetBox="[172,1421,359,1891]" captionTargetId="figure-102@14.[152,1436,345,1907]" captionTargetPageId="14" captionText="FIGURE 5. A–C. Pristonesia sicril sp. nov.; D–F. Pristonesia tainatril sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia uvenil sp. nov.. A, D, G. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410670" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410670/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">5D</figureCitation>
)........................................................................................ 4
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
</keyStep>
<keyStep id="30A9A4FBFFF91568E7F21B27FA3A38BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21B27FA3A3880" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21B27FA3A3880" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
3. Lobes of posterior hypopygeal margin outcurved, with small conical spine (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E4DC1B27FBA0386D" box="[953,1030,850,872]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Fig. 4D</figureCitation>
); harpe with median projection (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E25A1B27FA20386D" box="[1343,1414,850,872]" captionStart="FIGURE 4" captionStartId="13.[151,250,1943,1967]" captionTargetBox="[240,1348,198,1903]" captionTargetId="figure-17@13.[228,1360,181,1920]" captionTargetPageId="13" captionText="FIGURE 4. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov., J-L. Pristonesia querfil sp. nov.. A, D, G, J. Hypopygium, external view; B, E, H, K. Genitalia, dorsal view; C, F, I, L. Genitalia, ventral view. Black = cupula; dark grey = ventral valvae; light grey = apical membranous bubble. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6411093" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6411093/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Fig. 4F</figureCitation>
)....................................................................................... 
<taxonomicName id="4C5DC7DDFFF91568E39C1B05FAEF3880" authority="Azevedo &amp; Colombo, 2022" authorityName="Azevedo &amp; Colombo" authorityYear="2022" box="[1273,1353,880,901]" class="Insecta" family="Bethylidae" genus="Pristonesia" kingdom="Animalia" order="Hymenoptera" pageId="2" pageNumber="323" phylum="Arthropoda" rank="species" species="oracil" status="sp. nov.">
<emphasis id="B929604CFFF91568E39C1B05FAEF3880" box="[1273,1353,880,901]" italics="true" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">P. oracil</emphasis>
</taxonomicName>
<emphasis id="B929604CFFF91568E2351B05FA3A3880" bold="true" box="[1360,1436,880,901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<taxonomicNameLabel id="A21ADD37FFF91568E2351B05FA3A3880" box="[1360,1436,880,901]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323" rank="species">sp. nov.</taxonomicNameLabel>
</emphasis>
</keyLead>
</paragraph>
<paragraph id="8BE2BC5EFFF91568E7F21BF8FA3A38BA" blockId="2.[151,1437,616,1312]" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
<keyLead id="30AC1F6BFFF91568E7F21BF8FA3A38BA" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">
- Lobes of posterior hypopygeal margin angulate, without any spine (
<figureCitation id="1366A0DBFFF91568E4091BF8FC0938A6" box="[876,943,909,931]" captionStart="FIGURE 1" captionStartId="4.[151,250,1931,1955]" captionTargetBox="[152,1434,182,1908]" captionTargetId="figure-29@4.[151,1435,181,1908]" captionTargetPageId="4" captionText="FIGURE 1. A–C. Pristonesia nyamuragira Benoit; D–F. Pristonesia oracil sp. nov.; G–I. Pristonesia parcetil sp. nov.. A, D, G. Habitus, lateral view; B, E, H. Head, dorsal view; C, F, I. Mesosoma dorsal view. Scale bars = 100 µm." figureDoi="http://doi.org/10.5281/zenodo.6410624" httpUri="https://zenodo.org/record/6410624/files/figure.png" pageId="2" pageNumber="323">Fig. 1J</figureCitation>
); harpe without median projection (
